only have a red packet.

556
00:27:51,090 --> 00:27:52,360
I want a red packet.

557
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:53,630
Hey.

558
00:27:54,130 --> 00:27:56,030
Thanks for your generosity, boss.

559
00:27:56,030 --> 00:27:57,040
Don't be smug.

560
00:27:57,130 --> 00:27:58,310
We must use the money wisely.

561
00:27:58,310 --> 00:27:59,720
Save it for your mum's medical expenses.

562
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,090
Then you shall keep it.

563
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:02,190
Okay.

564
00:28:02,280 --> 00:28:04,280
Keep it up for next year.

565
00:28:04,370 --> 00:28:05,830
You're awesome this year.

566
00:28:07,100 --> 00:28:08,370
Thanks, boss.

567
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:11,240
-Thanks, boss.
-Wait for your turn.

568
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:14,100
Where's Jia Yun?

569
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:15,540
-Jia Yun.
-Jia Yun.

570
00:28:15,630 --> 00:28:18,340
-No idea.
-She left after answering a call.

571
00:28:18,430 --> 00:28:20,270
Doesn't she want this?

572
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:21,610
Just give it to me.

573
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:23,790
-I'll keep it for her.
-You're the boss.

574
00:28:23,790 --> 00:28:26,610
-I appreciate your hard work.
-Thanks.

575
00:28:26,780 --> 00:28:28,110
Everyone else gets one.

576
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:32,300
-So many.
-Aren't these for me?

577
00:28:32,300 --> 00:28:34,100
-Not for you.
-I just want it all.

578
00:28:35,650 --> 00:28:37,320
-These are for everyone.
-Stop being bossy.

579
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,230
-Return them to me.
-They're mine.

580
00:28:39,230 --> 00:28:40,660
Stop it.

581
00:28:40,750 --> 00:28:41,920
He's taken all of them.

582
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:43,100
Watch him, Yu Shi.

583
00:28:43,190 --> 00:28:44,770
Don't try to run away.

584
00:28:56,610 --> 00:28:59,820
[B2, Live for You, Cloud Live]

585
00:29:48,890 --> 00:29:50,210
Chen Lang.

586
00:29:58,070 --> 00:30:00,270
You're still sleeping during the day.

587
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:02,930
Never expect you would come.

588
00:30:06,620 --> 00:30:08,950
Help me carry these.

589
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,080
What are those?

590
00:30:10,160 --> 00:30:12,100
They're heavy.

591
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:14,530
What have you brought?

592
00:30:14,620 --> 00:30:16,290
My hands are now red.

593
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:18,240
Are you all right?

594
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:20,290
What are these?

595
00:30:20,510 --> 00:30:21,420
Bamboo shoots?

596
00:30:21,500 --> 00:30:22,650
You just came back from hometown?

597
00:30:22,650 --> 00:30:23,790
Last time I went back,

598
00:30:23,790 --> 00:30:25,880
didn't you refuse to
give your mum your address?

599
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,140
So she got mine instead

600
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:28,920
and sent me lots of delicious goodies.

601
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,980
She's wanted you to have a share, too.

602
00:30:31,210 --> 00:30:33,810
That's why I never
give my mum this address.

603
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:35,170
Didn't expect she'd send them to you.

604
00:30:35,170 --> 00:30:36,240
Thanks.

605
00:30:36,330 --> 00:30:37,270
It's nothing.

606
00:30:37,350 --> 00:30:38,450
The bamboo shoots

607
00:30:38,540 --> 00:30:40,270
are best for hot pot.

608
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:42,470
I also bought lots of meat and vegetables.

609
00:30:42,470 --> 00:30:44,260
Let's have hot pot today.

610
00:30:44,350 --> 00:30:45,760
Oh my.

611
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:48,590
Sure.

612
00:30:48,790 --> 00:30:50,860
The door was open when I came in.

613
00:30:50,950 --> 00:30:52,290
What if the thieves sneaked in?

614
00:30:52,290 --> 00:30:53,430
What's there to steal?

615
00:30:53,430 --> 00:30:54,750
I have nothing now.

616
00:30:54,980 --> 00:30:56,910
Except for my body, if they want it.

617
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,810
Not bad, you still could joke.

618
00:31:00,330 --> 00:31:01,790
I didn't bring a pot.

619
00:31:01,870 --> 00:31:03,190
Do you have one?

620
00:31:05,430 --> 00:31:06,670
I may have one in the kitchen.

621
00:31:06,670 --> 00:31:07,690
Okay.

622
00:31:07,780 --> 00:31:09,710
Make yourself at home.

623
00:31:13,830 --> 00:31:15,080
Why do you think

624
00:31:15,170 --> 00:31:18,160
we left our depressing hometowns

625
00:31:18,430 --> 00:31:19,610
for the big city?

626
00:31:19,690 --> 00:31:22,030
It's to make money

627
00:31:22,510 --> 00:31:24,160
and make our folks

628
00:31:24,250 --> 00:31:25,850
and ourselves proud.

629
00:31:25,940 --> 00:31:27,390
And to retire in style.

630
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,910
No wonder you'd rather stay here

631
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,130
during the festival

632
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:33,550
than to go back.

633
00:31:40,550 --> 00:31:41,870
I wish to be back, too.

634
00:31:43,430 --> 00:31:45,370
See what I've done to my company.

635
00:31:45,610 --> 00:31:47,340
It's now ruined beyond repair.

636
00:31:47,350 --> 00:31:48,890
I won't be able to face them.

637
00:31:50,210 --> 00:31:51,810
On the contrary.

638
00:31:51,900 --> 00:31:54,070
Your family is still proud
of you no matter what.

639
00:31:54,070 --> 00:31:56,800
That's even a more valid
reason for me not to do so.

640
00:32:00,220 --> 00:32:01,880
I think you're totally wrong.

641
00:32:03,300 --> 00:32:05,850
You were able to pull yourself up

642
00:32:05,940 --> 00:32:07,150
by your bootstraps.

643
00:32:07,230 --> 00:32:09,030
That's already an amazing feat.

644
00:32:19,930 --> 00:32:21,970
After visiting your home,

645
00:32:22,060 --> 00:32:24,440
I'm now able to find out
who you really are.

646
00:32:25,160 --> 00:32:28,600
I saw your childhood and
your track of growing up.

647
00:32:30,130 --> 00:32:32,200
I had the very first attempt to understand

648
00:32:32,200 --> 00:32:33,960
your desire for success.

649
00:32:34,130 --> 00:32:36,820
You're carrying too many
missions on your shoulders.

650
00:32:36,820 --> 00:32:38,130
That's why

651
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:40,350
your pressure got increasingly huge.

652
00:32:47,210 --> 00:32:49,270
How's your grad school application?

653
00:32:54,420 --> 00:32:56,270
So-so, I guess.

654
00:32:57,430 --> 00:33:00,660
Anyway, the processes are complicated.

655
00:33:00,750 --> 00:33:01,990
We'll see.

656
00:33:03,250 --> 00:33:04,650
No rush.

657
00:33:12,220 --> 00:33:13,410
Here.

658
00:33:14,180 --> 00:33:17,570
Your mum wants you to have this.

659
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,750
My mum dug this bamboo
shoot with her own hands.

660
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:22,790
And you put it in my bowl.

661
00:33:22,790 --> 00:33:24,200
This is so delicious.

662
00:33:25,190 --> 00:33:26,140
So

663
00:33:26,220 --> 00:33:28,020
you should visit her more often.

664
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:31,340
Anyway, the old folks won't
have much material needs.

665
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,500
What about you?

666
00:33:34,220 --> 00:33:36,910
You hardly go back to hometown, too.

667
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:42,340
Tell me.

668
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:44,990
Just tell me honestly.

669
00:33:44,990 --> 00:33:46,820
You love me all along, don't you?

670
00:33:46,900 --> 00:33:48,230
That's why you're here.

671
00:33:51,610 --> 00:33:53,250
Stop being smug.

672
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:56,810
I'm only here to deliver
your mum's bamboo shoots.

673
00:33:56,900 --> 00:33:59,060
Like I said, they go bad quickly.

674
00:34:00,680 --> 00:34:02,130
I see.

675
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:04,120
You usually make acquaintance

676
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,690
with the rich and powerful.

677
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:07,460
You'd never visit a small fry like me,

678
00:34:07,460 --> 00:34:10,060
especially now that I've hit rock bottom.

679
00:34:10,150 --> 00:34:13,580
I'm not that kind of person.

680
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,219
I only make friends with people

681
00:34:16,310 --> 00:34:18,199
that deserve my friendship.

682
00:34:23,389 --> 00:34:24,610
I must thank my mum.

683
00:34:24,699 --> 00:34:27,429
Otherwise, I won't get
to have this hot pot today.

684
00:34:28,290 --> 00:34:29,429
I think

685
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:31,570
your folks haven't had an easy life.

686
00:34:31,659 --> 00:34:33,420
They'll surely miss you.

687
00:34:33,989 --> 00:34:36,280
Just give them a call when you're free.

688
00:34:46,889 --> 00:34:49,000
Why do you think I strive so hard?

689
00:34:51,770 --> 00:34:53,489
I just want a better life.

690
00:34:55,150 --> 00:34:58,800
I'm building a foundation
for my future family.

691
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:02,350
And to give my folks a comfortable life.

692
00:35:04,150 --> 00:35:05,730
Our industry.

693
00:35:06,540 --> 00:35:08,230
The e-commerce industry.

694
00:35:09,300 --> 00:35:11,350
Today we may have the edge.

695
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:12,930
Who knows

696
00:35:13,030 --> 00:35:14,700
what will happen tomorrow?

697
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,060
As a new wave rises, an old wave falls,

698
00:35:17,110 --> 00:35:19,160
crashing on the beach.

699
00:35:19,250 --> 00:35:21,950
I'm like the old wave, dying in the sand.

700
00:35:22,040 --> 00:35:24,500
I think this is the
best thing about mankind.

701
00:35:24,540 --> 00:35:26,830
You see, one wave succeeds another.

702
00:35:26,910 --> 00:35:28,390
Each generation has its innovations.

703
00:35:28,390 --> 00:35:31,340
We continue to advance
and evolve this way.

704
00:35:33,500 --> 00:35:34,380
For me,

705
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:36,500
I believe the best always survives.

706
00:35:36,580 --> 00:35:38,980
It's all about the
survival of the fittest.

707
00:35:41,240 --> 00:35:43,660
I think it's the opposite.

708
00:35:44,810 --> 00:35:47,790
I wonder why humankind is
divided into different classes?

709
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:48,970
That's why

710
00:35:49,060 --> 00:35:51,300
there are so many wars and disasters.

711
00:35:51,390 --> 00:35:53,440
Why can't we all

712
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:55,720
get along and prosper together?

713
00:35:56,230 --> 00:35:57,200
Do you agree?

714
00:35:57,290 --> 00:35:58,740
I like your kindness

715
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:00,980
but it's too idealistic.

716
00:36:01,490 --> 00:36:04,790
People like us are beaten up by life.

717
00:36:06,100 --> 00:36:07,630
I shudder to think about it.

718
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:11,720
Actually, I didn't say this.

719
00:36:11,810 --> 00:36:13,910
I heard this from a friend.

720
00:36:13,990 --> 00:36:15,960
And he said it better than me.

721
00:36:16,050 --> 00:36:18,250
Really? What did he say?

722
00:36:19,430 --> 00:36:20,650
This is what he said.

723
00:36:20,740 --> 00:36:22,200
In this world,

724
00:36:22,290 --> 00:36:23,860
everyone is like a rabbit.

725
00:36:23,950 --> 00:36:26,420
Some are black while the others are white.

726
00:36:26,510 --> 00:36:29,250
However, when the black rabbit
runs, the white rabbit must run, too.

727
00:36:29,250 --> 00:36:31,930
We're using our gifts

728
00:36:32,020 --> 00:36:33,280
to make it in our lives.

729
00:36:33,350 --> 00:36:36,410
So there's no such thing as
the survival of the fittest.

730
00:36:37,020 --> 00:36:39,130
I like this statement.

731
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:42,250
This person should be quite interesting.

732
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,300
Then do you want to see him?

733
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:51,270
Today?

734
00:36:58,360 --> 00:36:59,540
Sure.

735
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:07,880
I suggest

736
00:37:07,970 --> 00:37:09,300
-we have a toast.
-Sure.

737
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:11,630
I'm drinking water instead of wine today.

738
00:37:11,690 --> 00:37:13,100
Only water for you.

739
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:15,640
I wish you all in the new year,

740
00:37:15,730 --> 00:37:17,530
health and good luck.

741
00:37:17,670 --> 00:37:19,600
Work harder for a successful career.

742
00:37:19,600 --> 00:37:21,280
-Thanks Uncle Duan.
-Here's to it.

743
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:22,860
Happy new year.

744
00:37:22,950 --> 00:37:25,000
-Xi Xi.
-Happy new year, Aunt Zhou.

745
00:37:25,090 --> 00:37:27,860
-Happy new year.
-Happy new year, Duan Ran.

746
00:37:29,270 --> 00:37:30,320
Shen.

747
00:37:30,410 --> 00:37:32,740
Thanks for everything.

748
00:37:32,950 --> 00:37:34,080
I know you like fish.

749
00:37:34,170 --> 00:37:36,230
So I specially ordered a fish for you.

750
00:37:36,290 --> 00:37:39,240
Aren't you too kind to me, Sister Zhou?

751
00:37:39,330 --> 00:37:41,960
Xi Xi and Ran Ran absolutely
had a challenging time previously.

752
00:37:41,960 --> 00:37:43,150
Please help yourselves.

753
00:37:43,150 --> 00:37:44,560
It's okay.

754
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,910
Don't worry. We'll take care of ourselves.

755
00:37:46,910 --> 00:37:49,080
He usually eats a lot.

756
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:53,180
He'll have rice and noodles.

757
00:37:53,270 --> 00:37:54,460
He likes rice so much.

758
00:37:54,460 --> 00:37:55,920
Just don't worry about us.

759
00:37:57,180 --> 00:37:58,460
Xi Xi.

760
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,730
You've only been CEO for a year,

761
00:38:01,150 --> 00:38:02,650
and you've gotten so thin.

762
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:04,100
I got thinner?

763
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:06,040
-I think so.
-Really?

764
00:38:06,130 --> 00:38:07,090
No, Dad.

765
00:38:07,180 --> 00:38:08,320
She was never fat.

766
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:10,470
I think she's malnourished.

767
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:13,600
My figure is perfect, okay?

768
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:16,010
Young people these days have it tough.

769
00:38:16,060 --> 00:38:17,380
I've seen it all.

770
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,430
By the way, the rascal

771
00:38:19,510 --> 00:38:21,540
has lost weight. You'll see.

772
00:38:22,210 --> 00:38:23,940
-He's back?
-Ding Ding is back?

773
00:38:24,180 --> 00:38:26,490
He suffers

774
00:38:26,580 --> 00:38:27,720
from jet lag.

775
00:38:27,810 --> 00:38:30,670
He couldn't wait to see Ran Ran and Xi Xi.

776
00:38:31,580 --> 00:38:33,580
Looks like he's now a changed person.

777
00:38:33,580 --> 00:38:36,380
Didn't expect he'd take
the initiative to meet us.

778
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,410
Ding Ding.

779
00:38:46,610 --> 00:38:48,100
You've become thinner.

780
00:38:49,410 --> 00:38:50,920
Hello, everyone.

781
00:38:51,010 --> 00:38:53,060
-Dad.
-You look handsome.

782
00:38:53,150 --> 00:38:55,220
Your hairstyle is really nice.

783
00:38:56,580 --> 00:38:58,340
Help yourself, Ding Ding.

784
00:38:58,430 --> 00:39:00,700
Shouldn't you inform us

785
00:39:00,780 --> 00:39:02,150
that you're back?

786
00:39:02,710 --> 00:39:04,040
Well,

787
00:39:04,130 --> 00:39:06,500
you should have at least

788
00:39:06,590 --> 00:39:07,910
informed us, right?

789
00:39:08,590 --> 00:39:10,740
What? Are we not important enough?

790
00:39:10,830 --> 00:39:12,180
I think so.

791
00:39:12,270 --> 00:39:13,680
That must be it.

792
00:39:14,890 --> 00:39:16,510
Look at Ding Ding.

793
00:39:16,730 --> 00:39:18,130
Now he's just like Ran Ran

794
00:39:18,190 --> 00:39:20,250
when he returned from overseas then.

795
00:39:20,250 --> 00:39:21,830
You like the local food better, right?

796
00:39:21,830 --> 00:39:24,340
I don't think he's become thinner.

797
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:32,180
Mind your words.

798
00:39:32,420 --> 00:39:34,030
You two always bullied Ding Ding
when you were kids.

799
00:39:34,030 --> 00:39:36,010
Now you've grown up and yet
you're still doing the same thing.

800
00:39:36,010 --> 00:39:37,880
No, we didn't. Have some more.

801
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:40,120
Don't mind them, Ding Ding. Eat up.

802
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:41,420
I'm done.

803
00:39:43,100 --> 00:39:45,300
Are you kidding?

804
00:39:45,390 --> 00:39:47,170
Eat some more.

805
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:48,670
You could use more weight.

806
00:39:48,670 --> 00:39:50,120
That's enough.

807
00:39:56,110 --> 00:39:57,550
Say,

808
00:39:57,640 --> 00:39:58,960
Chubby Ding.

809
00:39:59,550 --> 00:40:02,710
You've been a finance guy in the UK
for quite a while now.

810
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,500
You must've made a lot of money.

811
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:06,720
You should have visited
the Chinese restaurants

812
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:08,210
in Chinatown more often.

813
00:40:08,520 --> 00:40:10,770
His little deals are nothing

814
00:40:11,250 --> 00:40:12,660
compared to Duan Ran's business.

815
00:40:12,660 --> 00:40:13,670
and Xi Xi.

816
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,180
You're too humble.

817
00:40:15,260 --> 00:40:16,240
I heard

818
00:40:16,330 --> 00:40:19,190
Ding Ding set up an
investment company overseas.

819
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:21,350
How can we even compare?

820
00:40:21,350 --> 00:40:23,880
Meanwhile, we have to work so hard
to solicit funding

821
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,140
unlike this genius.

822
00:40:25,230 --> 00:40:26,460
Is that so?

823
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:28,560
Don't you have QE Group to back you?

824
00:40:28,610 --> 00:40:30,200
Why do you need to solicit funding?

825
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:31,120
So dishonest.

826
00:40:31,200 --> 00:40:32,700
Who'd invest in you?

827
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,430
Xi Xi is trying to be modest.

828
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:36,970
Can't you tell?

829
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:39,560
He still lacks experience.

830
00:40:47,950 --> 00:40:49,280
Where are you taking me?

831
00:40:49,310 --> 00:40:50,410
Who are we seeing?

832
00:40:50,500 --> 00:40:51,940
You'll know when we reach.

833
00:40:51,940 --> 00:40:53,030
Just trust me.

834
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:54,880
I've always trusted you.

835
00:41:13,370 --> 00:41:15,390
What kind of setup is this?

836
00:41:15,970 --> 00:41:18,350
Why are there four sets of tableware?

837
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:19,670
How many of them?

838
00:41:20,150 --> 00:41:21,700
The couple is having a meal here.

839
00:41:21,700 --> 00:41:24,720
I've invited them to
come after their meal.

840
00:41:24,810 --> 00:41:25,950
A couple?

841
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:28,070
It's unexpected.

842
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:29,690
Jia Yun.

843
00:41:29,780 --> 00:41:31,270
You're here.

844
00:41:32,260 --> 00:41:34,760
-We're late.
-It's okay.

845
00:41:34,850 --> 00:41:36,660
We've some snacks and tea here.

846
00:41:36,750 --> 00:41:38,340
-Jia Yun.
-Please take a seat.

847
00:41:38,340 --> 00:41:39,540
-Chen Lang.
-Mr Duan.

848
00:41:39,610 --> 00:41:41,610
-Long time no see.
-Long time no see.

849
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:44,940
Take a seat.

850
00:41:50,930 --> 00:41:52,680
Jia Yun has arranged today's meeting,

851
00:41:52,680 --> 00:41:54,610
I thought I'm going to see Duan Ran.

852
00:41:54,630 --> 00:41:56,430
I didn't expect it to be you two.

853
00:41:57,930 --> 00:41:59,180
Why?

854
00:41:59,270 --> 00:42:02,020
Is seeing me making you uncomfortable?

855
00:42:02,110 --> 00:42:03,140
Not at all.

856
00:42:03,230 --> 00:42:04,670
I'm flattered.

857
00:42:04,760 --> 00:42:06,080
I'm just flattered.

858
00:42:06,790 --> 00:42:08,550
Well, I actually have an
appointment with a couple of friends

859
00:42:08,550 --> 00:42:09,690
next door.

860
00:42:09,770 --> 00:42:10,920
I'm going over to meet them.

861
00:42:10,920 --> 00:42:12,250
Please excuse me.

862
00:42:12,340 --> 00:42:13,570
Let me walk you to the door.

863
00:42:13,570 --> 00:42:15,150
No, I'm fine.

864
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:16,660
Bye.

865
00:42:17,310 --> 00:42:19,020
-Thanks for coming.
-Bye, Jia Yun.

866
00:42:19,020 --> 00:42:20,120
Okay.

867
00:42:27,680 --> 00:42:28,690
What's going on with you?

868
00:42:28,690 --> 00:42:30,290
You should have informed me
when you invited Mr Duan Sr.

869
00:42:30,290 --> 00:42:32,000
I feel guilty meeting them.

870
00:42:32,090 --> 00:42:33,220
It's so embarrassing.

871
00:42:33,220 --> 00:42:34,820
No matter what, we're already here.

872
00:42:34,820 --> 00:42:37,550
Stop muttering in front of me.

873
00:42:37,750 --> 00:42:39,080
Let's sit down and chat.

874
00:42:44,630 --> 00:42:46,220
Mr Duan, I heard

875
00:42:46,300 --> 00:42:48,050
that you fainted during the negotiation.

876
00:42:48,050 --> 00:42:49,770
How are you now?

877
00:42:50,080 --> 00:42:51,210
It's just an old bug.

878
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:52,790
I'm quite used to it.

879
00:42:53,870 --> 00:42:55,150
Chen Lang.

880
00:42:55,300 --> 00:42:57,330
If I'm right,

881
00:42:57,610 --> 00:42:59,240
after the Sanya incident,

882
00:42:59,330 --> 00:43:02,630
this is our second meeting, right?

883
00:43:04,650 --> 00:43:06,540
Mr Duan,

884
00:43:06,810 --> 00:43:10,200
actually I don't deserve to meet you.

885
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:11,420
I understand.

886
00:43:11,500 --> 00:43:13,360
I've done some pretty bad things.

887
00:43:13,450 --> 00:43:14,610
I'm a real jerk.

888
00:43:14,690 --> 00:43:15,870
It takes time

889
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:17,950
to become a jerk, and it takes time

890
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:19,410
to turn over a new leaf.

891
00:43:19,500 --> 00:43:21,510
Even if I'm remorseful,

892
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:23,850
I can't redeem myself.

893
00:43:25,230 --> 00:43:26,790
Don't be so hasty to draw conclusions.

894
00:43:26,790 --> 00:43:28,050
In this world,

895
00:43:28,140 --> 00:43:30,400
there's always a chance for redemption.

896
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:34,790
First of all,

897
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:37,860
let me dispel your

898
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:39,670
misunderstanding about us.

899
00:43:40,820 --> 00:43:43,280
You, Ran Ran and Xi Xi.

900
00:43:43,440 --> 00:43:45,260
To me, you three

901
00:43:45,350 --> 00:43:47,240
are like my children.
